## How to read this

- **Bold class boxes** are **aggregate roots** — the consistency boundary
  for a single transaction. Each lives in exactly one BC (annotated in the
  note above each).
- **Solid composition arrows** (`*--`) indicate "contained inside" — the
  child entity has no identity outside its parent aggregate.
- **Dashed associations** indicate **reference by ID** — across aggregates
  and across BCs, references are by ID only, never by direct object link.
- `<<value object>>` stereotype marks types with no identity — equality
  by value, immutable.

